WEBVTT

00:03.085 --> 00:04.532
MAN: Previously, on "Freakish"...

00:04.538 --> 00:05.820
WOMAN: That thing killed Noodle.

00:05.826 --> 00:07.460
It ripped him up and it drank his blood.

00:07.466 --> 00:08.900
- It has to die.
- [growling]

00:08.906 --> 00:11.566
- LeSean: There's a problem.
- Okay, there are like 100 problems.

00:11.567 --> 00:12.864
Not like this.

00:12.870 --> 00:15.148
- Hey, how much more do you have?
- Less than a day.

00:15.154 --> 00:17.280
He's torturing my sister!

00:17.281 --> 00:20.992
We kept your sister
alive so we could survive.

00:20.993 --> 00:22.802
If it were me in that cage...

00:23.496 --> 00:25.084
I know what I'd want.

00:25.998 --> 00:27.421
I'm so sorry.

00:30.628 --> 00:33.672
<i>[eerie music]</i>

00:33.673 --> 00:38.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:39.303 --> 00:40.637
Jesus!

00:40.833 --> 00:42.038
Dude, it's just me.

00:42.044 --> 00:45.372
- Yeah, why are you sneaking up on me?
- I'm not "Sneaking up" on anyone.

00:46.853 --> 00:48.372
Whatever. I'll leave.

00:48.838 --> 00:50.038
[sighs]

00:50.044 --> 00:51.244
Wait.

00:53.860 --> 00:55.101
I'm sorry.

00:55.528 --> 00:57.996
I wasn't really expecting
anyone down here.

00:58.865 --> 01:02.033
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:02.034 --> 01:05.407
I just came down here to
see if everything's okay.

01:06.497 --> 01:09.434
She told me to kill her
before she hurt somebody.

01:09.440 --> 01:10.640
[screams]

01:10.646 --> 01:11.846
[growling]

01:13.556 --> 01:15.346
Nobody could do that.

01:15.352 --> 01:18.049
We both know there are people
here that could do that.

01:18.050 --> 01:19.760
Barrett's a douche.

01:19.761 --> 01:21.049
[growling]

01:22.190 --> 01:23.393
[sniffing]

01:23.399 --> 01:25.093
I can't let this go on.

01:25.652 --> 01:28.320
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:28.326 --> 01:29.970
Help me end this.

01:31.230 --> 01:33.899
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.998 --> 01:37.107
Lost and found is my new
favorite shopping destination.

01:37.113 --> 01:38.453
[LeSean sighing]

01:38.708 --> 01:39.908
You okay?

01:41.501 --> 01:42.701
LeSean?

01:43.785 --> 01:45.510
[sighing]

01:45.722 --> 01:47.214
Can I do anything to help?

01:53.321 --> 01:54.942
[door opening]

01:56.339 --> 01:59.424
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:59.425 --> 02:06.432
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:14.774 --> 02:17.455
LeSean, are you okay?

02:19.779 --> 02:22.177
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

02:22.183 --> 02:23.857
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.863 --> 02:25.522
- What's going on?
- We got to get out of here.

02:25.527 --> 02:27.159
No, won't you tell me what's wrong.

02:27.165 --> 02:28.790
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:29.334 --> 02:30.534
LeSean!

02:30.540 --> 02:32.130
Hey, hey. Hey, LeSean. Stop.

02:32.136 --> 02:33.863
- Stop. Tell me, what's with you?
- Baby, they're inside.

02:33.868 --> 02:35.621
- Who's inside?
- Noodle, the others... they're in here.

02:35.626 --> 02:37.126
- We got to get out!
- Hey!

02:37.132 --> 02:40.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:41.467 --> 02:42.852
Did the right thing.

02:44.971 --> 02:46.378
I hope so.

02:46.644 --> 02:47.844
Ah!

02:47.850 --> 02:49.474
[grunting]

02:49.475 --> 02:50.675
I think he's seeing things.

02:50.681 --> 02:51.881
We got to get out!

02:51.887 --> 02:55.007
- It's not safe!
- [grunting]

02:55.124 --> 02:56.750
He thinks the freaks are in here.

02:56.756 --> 02:59.068
Yeah, there will be freaks
in here if he doesn't stop.

02:59.074 --> 03:01.056
We're gonna die! We
got to get out of here!

03:01.982 --> 03:03.689
Go, go! Get him! I got this.

03:03.695 --> 03:05.201
Come on, quick. Give me the board.

03:05.700 --> 03:07.213
- [growling]
- Come on.

03:07.219 --> 03:08.524
Come on, come on, come on.

03:09.207 --> 03:10.745
[Man growling]

03:10.746 --> 03:12.794
- Mary is loose again.
- No kidding.

03:12.800 --> 03:14.365
- Well...
- [drill whirring]

03:14.371 --> 03:17.006
- [growling]
- She was our only chance

03:17.012 --> 03:18.715
to learn more about
them, and you let her go.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.417
Maybe you need to take a step back

03:20.423 --> 03:22.814
and let us finish this
before somebody gets hurt.

03:22.820 --> 03:24.119
[scoffs]

03:24.844 --> 03:31.766
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:31.767 --> 03:33.696
[grunts] Are you nuts?

03:33.702 --> 03:35.586
[panting]

03:36.001 --> 03:37.534
Don't try to stop me.

03:37.540 --> 03:39.958
[grunting]

03:40.192 --> 03:42.027
I can't let you through that door.

03:42.028 --> 03:48.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:48.605 --> 03:55.159
Sync & Corrections by <font color="#d61dfc">PetaG</font>
www.addic7ed.com

03:55.761 --> 03:57.141
Is he okay?

03:57.821 --> 04:00.627
I have never messed somebody
up like this, where it lasted.

04:00.633 --> 04:02.360
This isn't from getting punched.

04:02.446 --> 04:05.144
- You can't know that.
- Actually, I can.

04:05.228 --> 04:07.296
- Was he bitten?
- No.

04:07.302 --> 04:10.016
- Or exposed to the air outside?
- He's not changing, stupid.

04:10.022 --> 04:11.674
- I am simply trying...
- Shut up, Barrett.

04:11.679 --> 04:12.899
Guys!

04:13.195 --> 04:16.476
Zoe, if he's not morphing, then
please, tell us what he is doing.

04:19.910 --> 04:21.495
He needs insulin.

04:21.500 --> 04:23.102
He's diabetic?

04:24.103 --> 04:25.722
Oh, my c...

04:25.728 --> 04:28.709
He might have been hallucinating.
That can happen in the later stages.

04:28.710 --> 04:30.129
And you know this how?

04:30.587 --> 04:32.902
I did an anatomy project on diabetes.

04:32.908 --> 04:35.003
He said this can happen
if it gets really bad.

04:35.009 --> 04:36.510
Great, just great.

04:36.516 --> 04:38.886
This would've been nice to
know a little bit sooner.

04:38.887 --> 04:41.597
You're one to talk about
informing the group of an issue.

04:41.598 --> 04:44.112
So, he's got how long? One, two days?

04:44.118 --> 04:46.495
- More like hours, maybe.
- Don't say that.

04:46.501 --> 04:48.414
There's a thousand
students in this school.

04:48.420 --> 04:50.313
A thousand lockers. Teachers' desks.

04:50.319 --> 04:53.428
There's got to be insulin around here
somewhere. We will find it for him.

04:53.985 --> 04:55.735
If we don't, he'll die.

04:57.000 --> 05:03.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:05.997 --> 05:07.454
Need any help?

05:07.569 --> 05:08.896
Not from you.

05:10.252 --> 05:12.363
I'm sorry I voted with Barrett.

05:12.369 --> 05:14.675
You voted against Mary.

05:14.979 --> 05:18.202
And someday, I'll explain
why I did what I did.

05:18.208 --> 05:20.987
You know, if you feel so
bad about it, tell me now.

05:21.863 --> 05:23.190
I can't.

05:23.473 --> 05:24.869
Violet, you know Barrett.

05:24.875 --> 05:26.892
He doesn't give a shit
about anyone but himself.

05:26.898 --> 05:29.493
Trust me, I know firsthand
how low Barrett can be.

05:29.499 --> 05:31.204
Yet you decided to vote with him.

05:31.210 --> 05:33.575
- Stop! He made me vote for him.
- Made you?

05:33.650 --> 05:36.278
I was there. He didn't
make you do anything.

05:36.611 --> 05:39.777
There are other ways to force
people to do what you want.

05:42.780 --> 05:44.565
So he has something on you.

05:44.781 --> 05:46.890
- I can't say.
- You...

05:46.896 --> 05:49.455
Don't worry about it. I don't know
why I expect anything more from you.

05:49.460 --> 05:51.282
We've known each other less than a week.

05:51.288 --> 05:54.211
You don't owe me anything,
and you didn't know Mary.

05:54.212 --> 05:56.265
Grover, it's not that simple.

05:56.474 --> 05:57.881
It is that simple!

05:57.887 --> 06:01.427
You had a choice to protect yourself,
or to let somebody else get hurt.

06:01.428 --> 06:03.128
And you chose wrong.

06:08.894 --> 06:10.920
I'm so glad you're feeling better.

06:12.314 --> 06:13.689
I've missed you.

06:13.862 --> 06:15.951
[sighs] I see.

06:19.667 --> 06:21.771
Hey, you want to do this here?

06:21.777 --> 06:23.987
- Absolutely.
- This is a lot.

06:24.257 --> 06:25.664
I know I am.

06:26.620 --> 06:29.705
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

06:29.706 --> 06:34.737
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:34.743 --> 06:36.726
You should not let her do that.

06:37.213 --> 06:40.237
- Why not?
- Dude, look at her.

06:40.717 --> 06:42.134
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:42.135 --> 06:44.179
[growls]

06:52.394 --> 06:53.594
Wait.

06:55.985 --> 06:58.354
I got this one. I know the combination.

06:58.360 --> 07:00.381
Well, if it's yours,
why are we checking it?

07:01.080 --> 07:02.501
It's not mine.

07:11.416 --> 07:12.791
Look, man, I know this is harsh,

07:12.797 --> 07:15.172
but we don't have time
for a pity party right now.

07:19.208 --> 07:20.980
We got to find insulin.

07:29.302 --> 07:32.286
Merry Christmas to me.

07:35.287 --> 07:36.936
We should finish up.

07:40.688 --> 07:42.094
Straight, huh?

07:44.911 --> 07:46.520
To Mary and Lyle.

07:50.542 --> 07:52.366
- [gagging and coughing]
- [chuckles]

07:52.372 --> 07:53.674
Ugh.

07:54.347 --> 07:57.042
Ah... Lyle would think
that was hilarious.

07:57.043 --> 07:59.559
Yeah... so would Mary.

08:04.939 --> 08:06.245
Lay your head back.

08:07.951 --> 08:09.411
You got to save your strength.

08:10.133 --> 08:11.599
We're dying.

08:11.933 --> 08:13.265
Nobody's dying.

08:16.104 --> 08:19.148
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

08:19.149 --> 08:24.425
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:24.431 --> 08:25.841
You're nurturing.

08:25.847 --> 08:28.360
My boyfriend's sick. Of
course I'm taking care of him.

08:30.618 --> 08:33.330
This is the girls' bathroom.

08:33.336 --> 08:34.630
I know.

08:34.787 --> 08:36.991
If you were doing anything
but getting water for LeSean,

08:36.998 --> 08:38.505
I'd give you your privacy.

08:38.793 --> 08:40.818
You take care of your brothers too.

08:40.825 --> 08:43.630
That's not creepy at all that
you know about my brothers.

08:43.631 --> 08:47.619
You mentioned them in the
lobby after the explosion.

08:47.625 --> 08:49.704
You were worried your mother
wouldn't be able to calm them.

08:49.709 --> 08:51.536
Yeah, we're not talking about my family.

08:53.719 --> 08:57.683
Mayday. Can anybody out
there hear me? Mayday.

09:01.569 --> 09:04.659
Mayday. I'm at Kent High School.

09:05.737 --> 09:07.783
[gasps]

09:07.789 --> 09:09.105
You startled me.

09:09.491 --> 09:11.401
Doesn't seem to be reaching anyone.

09:11.701 --> 09:14.078
I may have to admit all
I've managed to fabricate

09:14.079 --> 09:15.981
is a machine that makes static.

09:33.223 --> 09:36.225
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:36.226 --> 09:42.564
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:42.565 --> 09:44.589
Go, baby, take a little sip.

09:45.174 --> 09:46.374
LeSean?

09:46.984 --> 09:48.259
Hey, wake up.

09:50.180 --> 09:52.596
Hey, hey, stay with me.

09:52.681 --> 09:56.983
[gasps] Stay with me.
Somebody help! Hey... please...

09:56.989 --> 09:59.759
- What's wrong?
- He's not waking up.

09:59.765 --> 10:01.194
LeSean?

10:01.751 --> 10:03.085
- [sobbing]
- LeSean, come on.

10:03.086 --> 10:04.582
- Wake up.
- What's happening?

10:04.588 --> 10:06.661
He's going into a coma,
which is what happens.

10:06.667 --> 10:08.067
Near the end.

10:08.652 --> 10:11.370
It's what happens near the end. Say it.

10:11.970 --> 10:13.666
I'm sorry. I really am.

10:14.264 --> 10:17.066
[sobbing] I can't lose him.

10:17.655 --> 10:19.161
I...

10:22.395 --> 10:25.794
Lyle's mom had diabetes. Lost her foot.

10:26.413 --> 10:27.920
Sounds awful.

10:30.113 --> 10:31.631
You knew him a long time?

10:32.712 --> 10:34.588
Yeah, since we were seven.

10:36.556 --> 10:38.573
His dad used to work at my dad's garage.

10:38.579 --> 10:39.987
[chuckles] Your dad...

10:39.993 --> 10:42.786
- I can't even picture Lyle as a kid.
- [both chuckle]

10:42.792 --> 10:44.566
Yeah, he was a little shit.

10:48.952 --> 10:50.938
You didn't find anything
on this floor, I take it.

10:50.944 --> 10:53.426
DIESEL: Nope, just a
whole bunch of rotten food.

10:53.647 --> 10:56.957
Oh, and the girl who was
into, uh, unicorns likes vodka.

11:00.602 --> 11:03.645
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

11:03.646 --> 11:10.695
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:23.837 --> 11:25.337
LeSean is getting worse.

11:25.343 --> 11:26.720
Then there's not much time.

11:26.726 --> 11:29.111
[sighs] Did you find anything?

11:29.714 --> 11:31.614
No. Nothing.

11:31.621 --> 11:36.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:40.975 --> 11:44.019
<i>[eerie music]</i>

11:44.020 --> 11:51.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:58.514 --> 12:00.105
Everything okay?

12:00.111 --> 12:01.311
GROVER: Yeah.

12:03.011 --> 12:04.515
Mary liked...

12:05.419 --> 12:06.861
likes...

12:09.421 --> 12:10.734
Liked?

12:11.116 --> 12:12.429
Airplanes.

12:13.322 --> 12:14.936
Real ones too?

12:16.736 --> 12:18.557
Thanks. Yeah.

12:19.329 --> 12:21.041
She liked taking trips.

12:22.058 --> 12:24.853
She always wanted a job
where she could travel a lot.

12:26.341 --> 12:27.656
Like a diplomat?

12:28.296 --> 12:29.734
Or a pilot.

12:30.702 --> 12:32.309
Or a salesperson.

12:33.223 --> 12:35.031
Or a professional musician.

12:35.037 --> 12:37.322
And... pro hockey.

12:40.829 --> 12:43.552
She seemed like someone who
could do just about anything.

12:48.053 --> 12:50.129
I'm sorry about what happened.

12:55.474 --> 12:56.775
It's weird.

12:58.471 --> 13:01.557
So many people might be dead.

13:01.563 --> 13:05.067
But somehow, thinking of
her as a freak is just...

13:06.156 --> 13:07.991
so much worse.

13:08.258 --> 13:09.544
I get it.

13:11.648 --> 13:13.971
I can't even picture Addy like that.

13:14.976 --> 13:16.969
I mean, they're not dead, but...

13:17.547 --> 13:19.534
they're not gone, either.

13:21.823 --> 13:23.864
I keep hoping there's a cure.

13:27.635 --> 13:28.962
Me too.

13:30.835 --> 13:32.535
[clicking]

13:42.117 --> 13:44.051
BARRETT: He'll need more soon enough.

13:44.057 --> 13:47.100
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:47.106 --> 13:54.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:09.801 --> 14:11.188
You going outside?

14:11.602 --> 14:13.207
I want to feel the air.

14:13.213 --> 14:16.000
You got to open the doors to go outside.

14:16.006 --> 14:19.012
I know. Can't stay in here.

14:19.081 --> 14:21.188
Go ahead. Try and get out.

14:26.461 --> 14:28.338
[growling]

14:34.899 --> 14:36.517
ZOE: His heartbeat's really weak.

14:37.419 --> 14:39.420
[sighs] I'm gonna go
check the gym lockers.

14:39.426 --> 14:41.135
Natalie and Violet already did that.

14:41.141 --> 14:42.692
Then I'm gonna go check
the nurse's office.

14:42.697 --> 14:43.915
We know there's none there.

14:43.921 --> 14:45.750
Okay, then I'm going
outside to a drug store.

14:45.751 --> 14:48.234
I understand why you're
upset, but acting impetuously

14:48.240 --> 14:50.409
- solves nothing.
- I can't just do nothing.

14:51.513 --> 14:52.713
Hey.

14:53.002 --> 14:54.420
This isn't necessary.

14:56.091 --> 14:58.484
My point is, you don't
have to search for insulin.

14:58.762 --> 15:01.969
Oh, my God. Oh, that's so great.
Where... where'd you find it?

15:01.975 --> 15:03.479
Principal Mitchell's office.

15:03.485 --> 15:04.985
Why didn't you say something sooner?

15:04.991 --> 15:07.265
I wanted to tell you when we were alone.

15:07.561 --> 15:09.562
I... I don't understand.

15:09.851 --> 15:12.236
There isn't really
anything to understand.

15:15.935 --> 15:18.346
- What do you want for it?
- Excuse me?

15:18.352 --> 15:20.831
What do you want for it?

15:21.424 --> 15:22.729
A "Thank you" will do.

15:22.735 --> 15:24.527
How am I supposed to thank you?

15:25.922 --> 15:27.738
I must admit, I'm a bit taken aback.

15:27.744 --> 15:29.325
Dude, just answer the question?

15:29.331 --> 15:31.136
I don't know if your
reaction is a reflection

15:31.142 --> 15:33.486
on how you see me, or you see yourself.

15:33.492 --> 15:35.713
- Either way, it's distressing.
- Stop talking like that

15:35.719 --> 15:37.127
and just give me the pen.

15:39.213 --> 15:41.042
I knew you didn't care for me.

15:42.119 --> 15:44.885
But to think me capable
of taking advantage of you,

15:44.891 --> 15:48.724
or for you to see yourself as something
to be bartered, like an object,

15:49.589 --> 15:51.980
I think you're
underestimating both of us.

15:51.986 --> 15:53.988
All I wanted was to help you and LeSean.

16:00.508 --> 16:01.798
Thank you.

16:02.314 --> 16:03.892
Go help your boyfriend.

16:04.780 --> 16:07.782
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:07.783 --> 16:12.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:21.862 --> 16:23.309
Hey.

16:23.315 --> 16:25.004
I was worried.

16:27.386 --> 16:29.171
[sighs]

16:29.513 --> 16:31.496
I thought I lost you.

16:37.203 --> 16:39.406
<i>[light rock music]</i>

16:39.412 --> 16:43.291
I give you warm canned cheese.

16:43.297 --> 16:45.080
- MAN: Ooh.
- MAN: Oh, that's my favorite.

16:45.086 --> 16:47.063
- And chips.
- GROVER: Chips?

16:47.069 --> 16:49.152
- NATALIE: I improvised.
- All right.

16:49.158 --> 16:52.244
SONG: ♪ ...ring around your finger ♪

16:52.245 --> 16:55.956
♪ Buy a bulletproof vest ♪

16:55.957 --> 16:57.249
- Pretty good.
- I mean,

16:57.250 --> 16:58.667
best waffle chip I ever had.

16:58.668 --> 17:01.270
I brought a little something extra.

17:01.276 --> 17:04.575
- Ooh, nice.
- LESEAN: Hey. Thank you, Diesel.

17:04.580 --> 17:06.675
Don't thank me. Thank the unicorn chick.

17:06.675 --> 17:07.958
[laughter]

17:07.964 --> 17:14.892
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:17.435 --> 17:19.723
- I'd like to make a toast.
- Here, here.

17:20.227 --> 17:21.656
To Barrett.

17:22.759 --> 17:25.227
You and I haven't
always seen eye-to-eye.

17:25.233 --> 17:27.505
I decided I didn't like
you before I knew you.

17:27.511 --> 17:29.022
You and me both.

17:29.193 --> 17:30.945
LESEAN: But I owe you my life.

17:32.222 --> 17:33.499
Thank you.

17:35.186 --> 17:36.389
To Barrett.

17:36.395 --> 17:38.222
- To Barrett.
- To Barrett.

17:39.294 --> 17:41.420
I would also like to make a toast.

17:43.592 --> 17:45.405
To everybody who we've lost.

17:47.303 --> 17:48.649
Mary.

17:49.107 --> 17:50.451
Lyle.

17:50.700 --> 17:52.002
Noodle.

17:52.228 --> 17:53.488
Addy.

17:54.537 --> 17:55.933
And all the others.

17:57.123 --> 18:00.167
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:00.173 --> 18:07.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:10.304 --> 18:13.422
One thing about being stuck here

18:13.974 --> 18:15.983
is that there's no normal.

18:16.474 --> 18:18.377
There are no funerals.

18:18.979 --> 18:20.462
No memorials.

18:21.940 --> 18:23.933
But we will do right by them.

18:25.822 --> 18:28.432
And we will remember them.

18:29.198 --> 18:31.240
[marker scraping]

18:31.241 --> 18:38.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:13.227 --> 19:15.454
My brothers are four years old.

19:17.538 --> 19:18.761
Cute age.

19:18.767 --> 19:20.278
You like kids?

19:22.244 --> 19:23.744
They're interesting.

19:25.120 --> 19:27.546
They see the world completely new.

19:27.663 --> 19:30.841
When my brother Patrick
first felt rain, he...[laughs]

19:30.842 --> 19:32.260
Completely freaked out.

19:32.261 --> 19:33.678
[laughs]

19:33.679 --> 19:36.180
He thought angels were
crying or something like that?

19:36.181 --> 19:39.100
He thought it wasn't gonna stop,
and we were all gonna drown.

19:39.101 --> 19:40.332
See?

19:40.686 --> 19:42.013
Interesting.

19:43.672 --> 19:44.885
Right.

19:45.098 --> 19:46.520
Um...

19:47.973 --> 19:49.799
I'm gonna go check on LeSean.

19:58.245 --> 20:01.264
So where did you find this insulin?

20:01.373 --> 20:03.195
In Principal Mitchell's fridge.

20:03.201 --> 20:04.421
Really?

20:04.427 --> 20:07.545
You didn't tell me you found
anything when you were in his office.

20:07.546 --> 20:09.505
I hadn't when I talked to you.

20:09.506 --> 20:11.704
Well, thank God you did.

20:11.710 --> 20:14.754
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:14.760 --> 20:21.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:30.694 --> 20:32.156
[giggling] Stop it.

20:32.162 --> 20:33.860
- You'd like a nice, tight, two-shot?
- No!

20:33.865 --> 20:35.359
[both laugh]

20:35.365 --> 20:36.858
- Hmm?
- No!

20:38.584 --> 20:40.694
I need to apologize to you guys.

20:41.693 --> 20:42.904
Yeah?

20:43.686 --> 20:45.334
[sighs]

20:45.876 --> 20:49.701
I'm sorry that I didn't tell
anybody that Mary was bitten.

20:51.923 --> 20:54.821
I don't really know if I knew
she was gonna turn into a freak,

20:54.827 --> 20:56.407
and I didn't want to admit it,

20:57.508 --> 21:00.390
or I just hoped she wouldn't, and...

21:00.396 --> 21:02.812
if I didn't say anything,
it would all get better.

21:02.818 --> 21:04.399
I get that.

21:08.815 --> 21:11.818
I'm so sorry about what
she did to Noodle, man.

21:11.943 --> 21:13.607
That's not your fault.

21:16.918 --> 21:18.544
Guys, we got a problem.

21:18.550 --> 21:19.831
Oh, God. What?

21:19.837 --> 21:21.222
The water's out.

21:21.228 --> 21:22.725
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:22.731 --> 21:23.983
Everywhere.

